      "side": 1,
      "message": "I conflated the exec.Command.Stdout/Stderr and osexec.Command.Stdout/Stderr.  I agree that it would be better to add some rules.  I wonder if it would be better to just remove CombinedOutput altogether.  I don\u0027t know what to do about LogStdout and LogStderr; we\u0027d have to disallow CombinedOutput or Stdout\u003d\u003dStderr if either are set, or use the ThreadSafeWriter.  That seems like more compromise than I\u0027d like.",
